1. Extract the year from all patient arrival dates.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: SELECT patient_id, YEAR(arrival_date) AS arrival_year
FROM patients;

2. Calculate the length of stay for each patient (departure_date - arrival_date).
ðð®ðžð«ð²: SELECT patient_id, name, DATEDIFF(day, arrival_date, departure_date) AS stay
FROM patients;

3. Find all patients who arrived in a specific month.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: SELECT MONTH(arrival_date) AS arrived_month, COUNT(*) AS total_patients
FROM patients
GROUP BY MONTH(arrival_date)
ORDER BY arrived_month;

ðƒðšð¢ð¥ð² ð‚ð¡ðšð¥ð¥ðžð§ð ðž:
Q: Calculate the average length of stay (in days) for each service, showing only services where the average stay is more than 7 days. Also show the count of patients and order by average stay descending.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: SELECT service, count(name) as count_of_patients, AVG(DATEDIFF(day, arrival_date, departure_date)) AS avg_interval_of_stay
FROM patients
GROUP BY service
HAVING AVG(DATEDIFF(day, arrival_date, departure_date)) > 7;
